				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="http://www.renewable-energysources.com/">http://www.renewable-energysources.com/</a></li>
					<li><a href="https://www.eia.gov/outlooks/aeo/pdf/electricity_generation.pdf">https://www.eia.gov...electricity_generation.pdf</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div><!--/Modal Biomass-->

<!-- Modal Geothermal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="Geothermal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="register form" aria-hidden="true">
	<div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
		<div class="modal-content">
			<div class="modal-header bg-secondary text-white">
				<h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLongTitle">Geothermal</h5>
				<button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
					<span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
				</button>
			</div>
			<div class="modal-body">
				<p class="text-dark">
					Generated from the heat of the eath's crust, these "hot spots" of the earth generate steam that is captured 
					and is able to turn genereators. The use of geothermal energy is largely based on the geographic make up of the
					land, and those major plants are located in the western United States. On a smaller scale, heat pumps are drilled into
					the ground to help cool and heat buildings. These ground-source pumps are the most effiecent method for heating and cooling. 
					As with solar, there is currently a high up-front cost, and as with buildings that were not built with this type on energy 
					in mind, the cost could be higher. 
				</p>
				<img class="my-3 img-fluid" src="~/img/rock1.jpeg" alt="Thermal Rock" />
				<h5 class="mb-4 text-dark">Cost Per Killowatt Hour: 5.55 cents</h5>
				<p class="text-dark">
					References/Additional Information:
				</p>
